## 🎯 SYSTEM OVERVIEW

### What is SyncWatch?

**SyncWatch** is a browser extension that synchronizes video playback across multiple users in real-time. When one user plays, pauses, seeks, or changes playback speed, all other users in the same "room" see the exact same video state instantly.

### Key Features

- ✅ Real-time video synchronization (play/pause/seek/speed)
- ✅ Multi-user rooms with unique names
- ✅ Video URL sharing between users
- ✅ **Real-time group chat within rooms** ← **NEW**
- ✅ **Chat history (last 100 messages per room)** ← **NEW**
- ✅ **System messages for join/leave events** ← **NEW**
- ✅ Netflix special support (via page script injection)
- ✅ Cross-browser support (Chrome, Firefox, Edge)
- ✅ Persistent WebSocket connections
- ✅ Auto-reconnect on network failure
- ✅ AFK (away-from-keyboard) detection

### Technology Stack

**Frontend (Extension)**:
- Manifest V3 (Chrome Extension)
- Vanilla JavaScript (no frameworks)
- Socket.IO Client (v4.7.5)
- HTML5 Video API

**Backend (Server)**:
- Node.js (v14+)
- Express.js (web server)
- Socket.IO (v4.7.5) (WebSocket)
- In-memory storage (or optional Redis/MongoDB)

