## 💬 CHAT FEATURE ← **NEW SECTION**

### Overview

The Chat feature allows users in the same room to communicate via text messages in real time. Messages are broadcast to all users, and a history of the last 100 messages is stored per room and sent to newly joining users.

### Message Types

| Type | Description | `user` field |
|------|-------------|-------------|
| `user` | Normal text message from a user | User's name |
| `system` | Auto-generated notification | `null` |

### System Message Triggers

| Event | System Message |
|-------|---------------|
| User joins | `"<name> joined the room"` |
| User leaves (normal) | `"<name> left the room"` |
| User disconnects unexpectedly | `"<name> disconnected"` |
| User kicked for AFK | `"<name> was disconnected (AFK)"` |
| Video shared | `"<name> shared a video: <title>"` |

### Server-Side Implementation

```javascript
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
// In your main Socket.IO handler block:
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

socket.on('join', (data) => {
  const { name, room } = data;

  // ... existing join logic ...

  // Send chat history to joining user
  const history = rooms[room]?.chatHistory ?? [];
  socket.emit('chatHistory', { messages: history });

  // Post system message to room
  postSystemMessage(room, `${name} joined the room`);
});

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
// NEW: Handle incoming chat messages
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
socket.on('chatMessage', (data) => {
  const roomName = socket.currentRoom;
  const userName = socket.userName;

  // Must be in a room
  if (!roomName || !userName) {
    socket.emit('error', 'socket_error_not_in_room');
    return;
  }

  // Rate limit check
  if (!checkSocketRateLimit(socket.id)) {
    socket.emit('error', 'socket_error_rate_limit');
    return;
  }

  // Validate
  if (!validateChatMessage(data.text)) {
    socket.emit('error', 'socket_error_message_invalid');
    return;
  }

  // Sanitize
  const sanitizedText = sanitizeInput(data.text);

  // Build message object
  const messageObj = {
    id: `msg_${Date.now()}_${Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 7)}`,
    user: userName,
    text: sanitizedText,
    timestamp: Date.now(),
    type: 'user'
  };

  // Store & broadcast
  appendToHistory(roomName, messageObj);
  io.to(roomName).emit('chatMessage', messageObj);
});

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
// On disconnect — post system message
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
socket.on('disconnect', () => {
  const { currentRoom, userName } = socket;
  if (currentRoom && userName) {
